Complaint:   The   collection,   analysis   and   disclosure   of   complainants   of   sexual   offences’personal information and the use of ‘consent’ statementsWe are writing to you to raise serious concerns about the access, collection, analysis and disclosure ofcomplainants of sexual offences’ personal information and the use of potentially coercive and overly-broad ‘consent’ statements by UK police forces and the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS). We havediscussed our concerns with the Centre for Women’s Justice and they support these submissions,although they will be be making their own additional submissions on this issue in due course.
